  "notes": "FY ends 28 February. FY results ~late April; interim (6m to ~end Aug) ~late September. CEO Graham Lee from 19 Jul 2025 (succeeded founder-era CEO Gerrie Fourie, retired 18 Jul 2025). SA's most valuable bank (~R498bn market cap, mid-June 2026). Highly diversified: FY2026 headline-earnings mix Personal Banking 41%, Insurance 27%, Fintech (VAS+Connect) 26%, Business Banking 5%, AvaFin 1%. Non-interest income = 67% of income after impairments. 26m active clients. AvaFin (international consumer lending) consolidated from 1 May 2024. Dividend policy: 55% of headline earnings. Reports IFRS in ZAR; overwhelmingly domestic/rand-funded. Audited unmodified (Deloitte & Touche + KPMG).",
